---
// [2] What The Standard Is — a quiet statement section. Faded emblem
// watermark behind the narrow column of serif body copy.
---

<section class="section definition" id="definition" aria-labelledby="definition-heading">
  <img
    class="definition__emblem"
    src="/images/gold-icon.webp"
    alt=""
    aria-hidden="true"
    loading="lazy"
    decoding="async"
  />
  <div class="container container--narrow definition__inner">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">What The Standard Is</p>
    <h2
      class="display display--lg definition__heading reveal"
      id="definition-heading"
      data-reveal-delay="0.05"
    >
      A protocol rulebook for allocated gold.
    </h2>

    <div class="definition__body reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.1">
      <p>
        The Global Gold Standard is the protocol rulebook for allocated gold. It
        defines how bars are registered, how claims are created, how Standard
        Metal Units are minted and burned, how liquidity routes through the
        market, and how participating vaults maintain control under shared
        rules. The result is simple: real metal stays in approved vault custody,
        while its value can move through a 24/7 global market.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .definition {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .definition__inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .definition__emblem {
    position: absolute;
    z-index: 0;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    width: min(72vw, 720px);
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    opacity: 0.1;
    filter: grayscale(1) brightness(0.55);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .definition__heading {
    margin-top: 0.5em;
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .definition__body {
    margin-top: clamp(28px, 3.6vw, 44px);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .definition__body p {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--serif-body);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 1.7vw, 1.45rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--char);
  }
</style>
